problem_statement:
Pivot with single aggregate ignores alias
### What happens?

This may be expected behavior, but I wanted to document it in case it is a bug!

When pivoting, aggregates included in the `USING` clause accept aliases. If only one aggregate is included in the `USING` clause, the alias is ignored. If multiple aggregates are included, the aliases are used.

### To Reproduce

```sql
-- Example dataset
CREATE TABLE Cities(Country VARCHAR, Name VARCHAR, Year INT, Population INT);
INSERT INTO Cities VALUES ('NL', 'Amsterdam', 2000, 1005);
INSERT INTO Cities VALUES ('NL', 'Amsterdam', 2010, 1065);
INSERT INTO Cities VALUES ('NL', 'Amsterdam', 2020, 1158);
INSERT INTO Cities VALUES ('US', 'Seattle', 2000, 564);
INSERT INTO Cities VALUES ('US', 'Seattle', 2010, 608);
INSERT INTO Cities VALUES ('US', 'Seattle', 2020, 738);
INSERT INTO Cities VALUES ('US', 'New York City', 2000, 8015);
INSERT INTO Cities VALUES ('US', 'New York City', 2010, 8175);
INSERT INTO Cities VALUES ('US', 'New York City', 2020, 8772);
```

Here, the alias is not used when creating column names:
```sql
PIVOT Cities ON Year USING SUM(Population) as total_pop;
```

| Country |     Name      | 2000 | 2010 | 2020 |
|---------|---------------|------|------|------|
| NL      | Amsterdam     | 1005 | 1065 | 1158 |
| US      | Seattle       | 564  | 608  | 738  |
| US      | New York City | 8015 | 8175 | 8772 |

Here, the alias is used:
```sql
PIVOT Cities ON Year USING SUM(Population) as total_pop, count(population) as count_pop;
```
| Country |     Name      | 2000_total_pop | 2000_count_pop | 2010_total_pop | 2010_count_pop | 2020_total_pop | 2020_count_pop |
|---------|---------------|----------------|----------------|----------------|----------------|----------------|----------------|
| NL      | Amsterdam     | 1005           | 1              | 1065           | 1              | 1158           | 1              |
| US      | Seattle       | 564            | 1              | 608            | 1              | 738            | 1              |
| US      | New York City | 8015           | 1              | 8175           | 1              | 8772           | 1              |

### OS:

Windows 10

### DuckDB Version:

v0.7.2-dev717

### DuckDB Client:

CLI

### Full Name:

Alex Monahan

### Affiliation:

DuckDB Labs and Intel

### Have you tried this on the latest `master` branch?

- [X] I agree

### Have you tried the steps to reproduce? Do they include all relevant data and configuration? Does the issue you report still appear there?

- [X] I agree
